parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: or refuses to shift gears; the vehicle loses power or acceleration; the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrates; the vehicle stalls or becomes stuck in gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt to extend or retract properly can lead to a safety concern, as passengers may not be able to properly wear their seatbelts, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear seat belt is locked up and will not extend
the rear seat belt will not retract without manual assistance
the buckle and slack seat belt get caught when the door closes
the seat belt cannot be properly fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belt can lead to a safety concern, as the driver or passenger may not be able to properly wear their seatbelt, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The front driver's seat belt stopped working
the front seat belt does not retract or extend properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective transmission can cause sudden loss of power, slipping, or failure to engage gears, leading to accidents, loss of control, or stranding the driver.
